title: For Sale:  Ruger Mini-14 Target Model. LNIB. Stainless. Heavy tunable barrel.
postcontent:
Ruger Mini-14 Target Model. Excellent. Laminate, ambidexterous thumbhole stock. Heavy stainless barrel.

 Harmonic barrel tuner that allows you to "tune" the barrel to your selected ammo. Check out vids on youtube.com and see just how accurate these guns are when dialed in. Its fun and easy. Once tuned, this gun is very accurate.  I'm barely an average shooter and I once dialed it in and got three in a row that could be covered easily with one of those target stickers about the size of a nickel. A good shooter would be incredible with this gun. Especially if you had a really nice scope to put on it. 

 Has LOP adjustable buttplates and Bushness XLT Trophy 3x9-40 scope. Does the job. Isn't a Leupold, but was $149.99.

 Have boxes and everything for the rifle and the scope including Ruger stainless rings. This gun has been fired right around 140 times if memory serves correct. 1/8 twist chrome-lined barrel. The gun as stated in the instructions and on the gun only shoots .223 ammo. I've read about people using NATO, but Ruger doesn't recommend it. This is a very nice gun and gets compliments from everyone who has seen it.

 Text is best at (515) 6six4-59seven8. Thanks.

I'd consider taking a revolver as trade if trading down or a couple handguns as trade.
